  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The improved Mask R-CNN network demonstrated advantages in segmentation accuracy, classification accuracy, and computational efficiency.",
    "Importantly, this optimization scheme can be well-applied not only to individual traffic scenarios like traffic signs and pedestrian detection but also to the detection of multiple objects in front of vehicles in autonomous driving environments, making it more practical.",
    "Reference [37] improved the initial YOLOv3 network model by adjusting the grid cell size, employing an enhanced k-means clustering algorithm, improving multiscale bounding box prediction, and using the Soft-NMS algorithm on the INRIA person and PASCAL VOC 2012 datasets, with a mean accuracy (mAP) of 90.42% and a mean processing time per frame was 9.6 ms.The improved algorithm exhibits accuracy and real-time performance, as well as robustness and anti-interference in complex scenarios.",
    "Reference [38] proposed the MobileNet-yolo algorithm, which addresses the limitations of the existing methods by optimizing the backbone feature extraction network, introducing the MFF model for information fusion, and incorporating the CBAM attention mechanism.",
    "This improves the accuracy of the YOLOV4-tiny model, which helps to protect the road safety of pedestrians, reduce traffic accidents, and ensure the stable Development of intelligent vehicle-assisted driving technology."
  ],
